Rating: 4
This salad is a wonderful combination of flavors. I sliced/shredded the brussel sprouts in a food processor and used Gala apples sprinkled with lemon juice. I'm not a big fan of blue cheese so I left that out. I served it with the baked pork chop menu from Bon Appetit Feb 2001. It was delicious.

Rating: 3
We liked this recipe a lot but we are huge fans of blue cheese and it is definitely a strong flavor in the recipe. There were a few too many brussel sprouts so I would cut back on those. This is also a salad that can be saved for leftovers as it keeps for a couple of days covered in the fridge. We will make it again!

